[ProMED-mail thanks the EpiCore Global Surveillance Project member for this update on the outbreak of a so far undiagnosed febrile illness among students at the Kumasi Academy.

Kumasi Academy is a public secondary boarding school located in Asokore-Mampong, a suburb of the city of Kumasi (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kumasi_Academy). Kumasi, with an estimated population in 2013 of over 2 million residents, is the capital of the Ashanti Region of Ghana (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kumasi). Maps of Ghana can be seen at http://www.ezilon.com/maps/images/africa/political-map-of-Ghana.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5491799,50377. The Ashanti Region is located in south-central Ghana and is 3rd largest of 10 administrative regions, with a population of about 3.6 million residents in 2000, accounting for 19.1 percent of Ghana's total population (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashanti_Region). - Mod.ML]
